==English==
===Etymology===
From the Norse [[Æsir]].
===Proper Noun===
'''Æsir''' (singular '''[[Áss]]'''; sometimes ''[[Aes]]'' by folk back-formation)
#the principal benevolent deities, as a group, of the Norse pantheon, representing power and war; opponents of the [[Vanir]].

==Norse==
===Etymology===
From the Proto-Germanic ''*Ansuz-''.
===Proper Noun===
'''Æsir''' (singular '''[[Áss]]''')
#the principal benevolent deities, as a group, of the Norse pantheon, representing power and war; opponents of the [[Vanir]].

